ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This is a math class. If you don't feel like math is important, then you should not take it. If you want to approach fluid mechanics problems in a classical theoretical approach, then this is what you must suffer through.
It is a class that teaches the fundamental principles governing fluid properties. I would not recommend this class to another student.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course is the crucible of Navier-Stokes. The work in the trenches seemed never ending and the problem sets went on ad infinitum. The material is obfuscated by a yoda like presentation of the fundamentals. By the end of the violence, my understanding had undergone a revolution. Because I study fluids, this was obviously useful.
